    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Clarify in `doc/descriptors.md` that the output key in `tr()` descriptors is computed by tweaking the internal key with the merkle root of the script tree (or nothing if no tree is provided), as defined in BIP 341\n- Add references to BIP 341 and BIP 386 for users who want the full specification\n\nCloses #30279\n\n## Motivation\n\nAs noted in #30279, the current documentation for `tr(KEY)` only states that `KEY` is used as the \"internal key\" without mentioning that the actual output key is the result of tweaking. This can mislead readers into thinking `KEY` is used directly as the output key. Pieter Wuille (sipa) agreed the docs should be more explicit and link to the relevant BIPs.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Verify BIP 341 and BIP 386 links resolve correctly\n- [x] Confirm the description accurately reflects the tweaking behavior",
